@inproceedings{ WOS:000326396402127,
Author = {Abdelaziz, Naglaa Sami},
Editor = {Chova, LG and Martinez, AL and Torres, IC},
Title = {SPECIALIZATION IN TEACHING THE LIGHTING DESIGN COURSES BETWEEN THE
   INTERIOR DESIGN PROGRAM AND THE ARCHITECTURAL ENGINEERING PROGRAM},
Booktitle = {INTED2012: INTERNATIONAL TECHNOLOGY, EDUCATION AND DEVELOPMENT
   CONFERENCE},
Series = {INTED Proceedings},
Year = {2012},
Pages = {2875-2883},
Note = {6th International Conference of Technology, Education and Development
   (INTED), Valencia, SPAIN, MAR 05-07, 2012},
Abstract = {In the past, the number of specializations never steps the dozen in
   itemize. Development of all kind of sciences, increasing of curriculums,
   expansion of discovered fields, these results increasing the complexity
   of disciplines to several divisions. Nowadays, as results, the focuses
   on the specific necessities became a must for any science - the variety
   of Noble Prices in different knowledge - as real example. One of the
   most important development methodologies, in any curriculum, is the
   introduction of new professional informative courses and topics.
   The basic information is in increasing integrations and interlinks
   between specializations, in particular, the co-specialization of
   interior design and architectural design. However there are a number of
   topics that should be focused, as points of interest, in each particular
   specialization; the main aims of this, is to reach the learning outcomes
   that follows the great amount of information in each topic and field.
   The interdisciplinary respect in any team work is the base to reach
   success; professional can't be replaced by others, due to the need of
   expert in each field.
   Lighting Design - the paper example - is an essential course in both
   programs; the Interior Design and the Architectural Design, is one
   example of such topic. Before it could be taught as similar topic for
   both programs, as the information were quiet enough. But at present
   condition, the quantity of profound informatics knowledge, and the need
   of many subtitles in each field, the matter of dividing their syllabus
   became a must. Lighting Design for interior Design program has a
   necessity to focus on different aspects and topics than for
   architectural design program.
   The interior design student need the basic information of natural and
   sustainable lighting design, so he/she could contribute in solving and
   deciding the opening based on the function and users needs; the interior
   design project program in all international institutions study these
   needs first then the architectural design project program apply its
   specific requirements. Moreover, the needs to study the types of
   lighting fixtures to suit the interior elements as function and concept
   of design, the needs of study the level of light need for each function
   based on the furniture arrangements and the interior treatment color
   schemes, the relation and affection of light on the color appearance,
   the standards data related to each specific interior functions, and for
   sure the types of lighting control to costume each user, all are vital
   topics needs thoughtful focus for the interior design students.
   While for the architectural design students, the important elements will
   start of sure with the natural and sustainable lighting design but with
   different aspects related moreover on the site, the buildings
   technologies, and the urban orientation. Then they will need to
   reflective core information of the lighting design for the building
   facades, the historical sites, the parking areas, the outdoors
   facilities, the complex building amenities, to success the target of
   those functions.
   From the precedents facts, this paper should reach a specific detailed
   syllabus, in the lighting design course, for each program; the interior
   design program and the architectural design program, in order to
   graduates professional ready with all developed science.},
